{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-08-10",
 "title": "A Favor for an A-Wing",
 "summary": "Returning to her office aboard the NRSC Deliverance after a patrol, Colonel Altair Quila is startled to find Bazil McKenzie -- in full NRI black -- waiting in the dark. He has come to ask her help with a delicate matter: Intelligence wants to hire the Sullustan pilot Enb'Zik, who in return requests an unmarked used A-wing and a place flying alongside the Republic squadrons in the final assault on the Death Star. Altair argues practical concerns -- an unmarked spy ship would be wasted in open battle -- and they compromise that Zik fly a standard fighter for the assault while keeping his A-wing for intelligence work, pending Arands's approval. The conversation turns to the Death Star itself, with Bazil candidly admitting Intel is still struggling to find a way aboard the station, and the two share their dread for Ithor's impending fate as its evacuation proceeds.",
